    <item>
      <title>Sugar Free Peach Jam</title>
      <link>https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/</link>
      <comments>https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/#comments</comments>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[Marisa McClellan]]></dc:creator>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Aug 2022 13:52:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://foodinjars.com/?post_type=recipe&amp;p=26166</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Looking for a sugar free peach jam recipe that is spreadable, satisfying, and bursting with summer fruit flavor? You&#8217;ve found it! This post is sponsored by Mrs. Wages. For years and years, there have been a subset of people who have written to ask me about making jam with sugar substitutes. I tried a handful [&#8230;]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><em>Looking for a sugar free peach jam recipe that is spreadable, satisfying, and bursting with summer fruit flavor? You&#8217;ve found it!</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="707" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26167" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal-1060x707.jpg" alt="Four pint jars of sugar free peach jam" class="wp-image-26167" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal-1060x707.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal-720x480.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal-768x512.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/four-jars-sugar-free-jam-horizontal.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p><em>This post is sponsored by Mrs. Wages. </em></p>



<p>For years and years, there have been a subset of people who have written to ask me about making jam with sugar substitutes. I tried a handful of times with stevia and monkfruit, but I never liked the results enough to share them here. But the folks from Mrs. Wages recently sent me a box of mixes and pectins that included a couple packets of their <a href="https://www.mrswages.com/product/mrs-wages-lite-fruit-pectin-home-jell/" rel="sponsored nofollow">Sugar Free Fruit Pectin Home Jell</a> and I was inspired to try again. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="707" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26185" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product-1060x707.jpg" alt="Two pint jars of sugar free peach jam and three boxes of Mrs. Wages Sugar Free Fruit Pectin Home Jell" class="wp-image-26185" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product-1060x707.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product-720x480.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product-768x512.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/mrs-wages-jars-and-product.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>This time, I tried it with the non-sugar sweetener Swerve and found that in combination with ripe peaches, a little apple juice, bottled lemon juice, some spices, and the sugar free pectin, produced a really balanced and beautifully set sugar free peach jam. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="795" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26178" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-795x1060.jpg" alt="Ripe peaches in a white enamel pan" class="wp-image-26178" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-795x1060.jpg 795w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-540x720.jpg 540w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peaches-in-a-pan-1-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></figure>



<p>With any peach jam, I started by peeling peaches (four pounds, to be precise). I cut them in half, removed the pits and arranged them cut side down on a deep baking sheet. Then I poured water from a freshly boiled tea kettle over the peaches and let them sit for two minutes. When the time was up, I carefully drained away the hot water and ran cool tap water over the peaches. The peels (mostly) slide right off. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="707" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26171" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan-1060x707.jpg" alt="Peeled peach halves in a white enamel pan, sitting in a sunny spot. " class="wp-image-26171" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan-1060x707.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan-720x480.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan-768x512.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/peeled-peaches-in-a-pan.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>Once the peaches were peeled, I slid them into an 8 quart Dutch oven and used a potato masher to break them into small bits. I added 1 cup of apple juice, 1/3 cup bottled lemon juice, and one packet Mrs. Wages Sugar Free Fruit Pectin Home Jell and let it sit for ten minutes. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="795" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26174" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-1060x795.jpg" alt="Ingredients for sugar free peach jam. Mashed peaches and apple juice in a pot, bottled lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, a box of pectin, and a measuring cup with Swerve alternative sweetener. " class="wp-image-26174" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-1060x795.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-720x540.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-768x576.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/final-ingredient-shot-scaled-e1661823732347-500x375.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>Normally, when you add sugar to fruit, it draws out the liquid and helps to prevent burning. But sugar-free sweeteners don&#8217;t have the same effect and what&#8217;s more, you don&#8217;t want to boil them for long, as that can render them bitter. So the juice is a critical element in getting a sufficiently cooked peach consistency. I made a couple of really unsatisfying batches before I figured out this trick. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="795" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26175" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-1060x795.jpg" alt="Close up on jars of spices for sugar free peach jam. " class="wp-image-26175" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-1060x795.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-720x540.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-768x576.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/ingredients-for-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled-e1661823810483-500x375.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>Once the fruit had a chance to sit and mellow with the pectin, I set the pot on the stove and brought it up to a hard boil. As it worked its way up to a boil, I added 1 teaspoon of cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon of ground cloves, and 1/2 teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg. </p>



<p>When it reached a hard boil, I set a timer for 1 minute and removed the pot from the heat the moment the time was up (the Mrs. Wages instructions stress the importance of not overcooking the pectin, as that could hinder its ability to set). </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="795" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26176" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-795x1060.jpg" alt="Stainless steel Dutch oven with sugar free peach jam, a grey ladle, and a black spatula inside. " class="wp-image-26176" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-795x1060.jpg 795w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-540x720.jpg 540w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cooked-sugar-free-peach-jam-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></figure>



<p>Finally, with the pot off the stove, I stirred in 1 1/4 cups Swerve (though you can obviously use your non-sugar sweetener of choice). Then, it was just a matter of funneling the jam into hot pint jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace. Wipe the rims, apply new lids and rings, and process in a boiling water bath canner for 10 minutes (<a href="https://foodinjars.com/blog/canning-101-on-adjusting-for-altitude/">adjusting for altitude</a> if you live above 1,000 feet in elevation). </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="795" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26177" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-795x1060.jpg" alt="Four pint jars of sugar free peach jam in a beige enamel canning pot. " class="wp-image-26177" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-795x1060.jpg 795w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-540x720.jpg 540w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/sugar-free-peach-jam-in-canner-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></figure>



<p>After the processing time is up, turn off the heat, remove the lid and let the jars rest in the cooling water for five minutes. Then remove the jars and set them to cool on a folded kitchen towel or wooden board. Let them sit until they are completely cool and then check seals. Sealed jars can be stored in your pantry, any with failed seals should be refrigerated and used promptly. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="707" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/sugar-free-peach-jam/?tp_image_id=26169" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical-707x1060.jpg" alt="Close up on one pint of sugar free peach jam" class="wp-image-26169" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical-707x1060.jpg 707w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical-480x720.jpg 480w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/hero-jar-sugar-free-peach-jam-vertical.jpg 1067w" sizes="(max-width: 707px) 100vw, 707px" /></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Troubleshooting Sugar Free Jam</h2>



<p>Don&#8217;t worry if you notice that the jam looks a little runny when it first comes out of the canner. Mine took a full day to reach set. Also, remember that sugar-free jams spoil more quickly than those with traditional portions of sugar. If a pint jar is too much for your household to use within a couple of weeks, consider using half pint or even 4 ounce jars. That way, you&#8217;ll be able to eat through the jar before it starts to get moldy. </p>



<p>I am delighted to have found a way to make a satisfying and delicious sugar-free jam. I hope you like it just as much as I do! </p>



