      <title>Getting Back to Blogging</title>
      <link>https://foodinjars.com/blog/getting-back-to-blogging/</link>
      <comments>https://foodinjars.com/blog/getting-back-to-blogging/#comments</comments>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[Marisa McClellan]]></dc:creator>
      <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jun 2022 02:10:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <category><![CDATA[canning]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://foodinjars.com/?p=25943</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Hello friends! Goodness, it sure has been a long time, hasn&#8217;t it. Between the pandemic, parenting, and burnout from all those sponsored posts last year, I forgot how to show up here. But after a little break, and the blessed addition of a regular babysitter, I&#8217;m finding myself itching to reclaim my identity and role [&#8230;]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="702" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/getting-back-to-blogging/?tp_image_id=26009" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-1060x702.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-26009" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-1060x702.jpeg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-720x477.jpeg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-768x509.jpeg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-1536x1017.jpeg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/blackberries-and-currants-2048x1356.jpeg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>Hello friends! Goodness, it sure has been a long time, hasn&#8217;t it. Between the pandemic, parenting, and burnout from all those sponsored posts last year, I forgot how to show up here. But after a little break, and the blessed addition of a regular babysitter, I&#8217;m finding myself itching to reclaim my identity and role as a canning blogger/writer/teacher. I knew it was time to get back to work when I started composing blog posts and recipe headnotes in my dreams. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="707" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/getting-back-to-blogging/?tp_image_id=26010" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-707x1060.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-26010" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-707x1060.jpg 707w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-480x720.jpg 480w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/vertical-strawberries-scaled.jpg 1707w" sizes="(max-width: 707px) 100vw, 707px" /></figure>



<p>Part of my motivation in returning to this space is that I&#8217;m seeing a big uptick in people looking to learn how to can. And I get that. Food prices are out of control and the state of the world feels precarious. Folks often turn to food preservation as a way of managing costs and creating a sense of security when things are desperately uncertain. I want to be here as a resource to help people can safely and deliciously. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="707" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/getting-back-to-blogging/?tp_image_id=26011" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-1060x707.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-26011" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-1060x707.jpeg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/DSC_1690-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>I&#8217;m also getting my (entirely free!) newsletter going again. It will go out on a monthly basis with reminders of seasonal recipes from the archives, as well as new-to-you bonus recipes. The first one goes out this Wednesday, so if <a href="https://foodinjars.com/newsletter-subscription/">make sure to subscribe</a> if you want my small batch recipe for Peach Rosemary Jam. </p>



<p> </p>
