    <item>
      <title>Mulled Apple Cider Syrup</title>
      <link>https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/</link>
      <comments>https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/#comments</comments>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[Marisa McClellan]]></dc:creator>
      <pubDate>Fri, 31 Dec 2021 03:21:54 +0000</pubDate>
      <category><![CDATA[drinks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Ball Home Canning]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Mulled Apple Cider Syrup]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://foodinjars.com/?post_type=recipe&amp;p=25623</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Make a batch of mulled apple cider syrup to keep in your fridge. You&#8217;ll be ready for festive sparkling drinks all season long. This post is sponsored by the makers of&#160;Ball home canning products.* Between fertility treatments, being pregnant, and time spent nursing, it&#8217;s been over than four years since I&#8217;ve had more than a [&#8230;]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><em>Make a batch of mulled apple cider syrup to keep in your fridge. You&#8217;ll be ready for festive sparkling drinks all season long. </em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="702" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25664" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled-702x1060.jpg" alt="Mulled apple cider syrup mixed with sparkling water in a Ball Flute Jar. " class="wp-image-25664" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled-702x1060.jpg 702w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled-477x720.jpg 477w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-syrup-angled.jpg 1060w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px" /></figure>



<p><em>This post is sponsored by the makers of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.freshpreserving.com/">Ball home canning products.</a>*</em></p>



<p>Between fertility treatments, being pregnant, and time spent nursing, it&#8217;s been over than four years since I&#8217;ve had more than a tiny sip of alcohol. In that time, I have developed a deep appreciation for syrups, shrubs, and other flavorful mixers that can bring easy interest to a glass of sparkling water. </p>



<p>When my friends at @ballcanning asked me to come up with something festive for the holiday season, my thoughts immediately landed on sharing my favorite mulled apple cider syrup. Combined with sparkling water and served in a&nbsp;<a href="https://bit.ly/3J7n1vG" rel="sponsored nofollow">Ball Flute Pint Jar</a>, it is fun, refreshing, and decidedly celebratory. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="702" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25626" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball-702x1060.jpg" alt="Mulling spices in a large, mesh tea ball. " class="wp-image-25626" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball-702x1060.jpg 702w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball-477x720.jpg 477w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/cider-spices-in-tea-ball.jpg 1060w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px" /></figure>



<p>Combine a half gallon of fresh apple cider in wide pot. Add some mulling spices. I used cloves, star anise, allspice berries, and cinnamon, contained in a tea ball for easy removal. Then bring it to a boil. You want to stay close as it comes up to a simmer, in order to skim the foam that will build on the surface. Once you&#8217;ve removed the foam, allow the cider to boil down for 45 to 60 minutes. You want the cider to reduce until you have about 12 ounces. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="702" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25625" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical-702x1060.jpg" alt="Mulled apple cider syrup, cooling in the pot. " class="wp-image-25625" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical-702x1060.jpg 702w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical-477x720.jpg 477w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/apple-cider-syrup-in-pot-vertical.jpg 1060w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px" /></figure>



<p>When it has reduced sufficiently, let it cool in the pot until room temperature. Once cool, pour into a <meta charset="utf-8"><a href="https://bit.ly/3EfwHR9" rel="sponsored nofollow">Ball Snowflake Keepsake Pint Jars</a>, cap with a <meta charset="utf-8">Ball Leakproof Storage Lid, and refrigerate until you&#8217;re ready to use it. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="702" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25666" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-702x1060.jpg" alt="Finished mulled apple cider syrup in a Ball Snowflake Jar. " class="wp-image-25666" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-702x1060.jpg 702w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-477x720.jpg 477w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree.jpg 1060w" sizes="(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px" /></figure>



<p>When you&#8217;re ready to build your drink, gather the syrup, a <meta charset="utf-8"><a href="https://bit.ly/3J7n1vG" rel="sponsored nofollow">Ball Flute Jar</a>, and some chilled fizzy water. Fill the jar three-quarters the way with sparkling water. Add a healthy dollop of apple cider syrup and a generous spoonful of pickled cranberries with their liquid. Stir to combine and add more sparkling water to fill the jar (you don&#8217;t want to add it all at the beginning because it will certainly bubble over while you&#8217;re mixing). </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="795" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25669" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-795x1060.jpg" alt="Mulled apple cider syrup in a Ball Flute Jar under a Christmas tree. " class="wp-image-25669" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-795x1060.jpg 795w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-540x720.jpg 540w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/sparkling-cider-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></figure>



<p>Here&#8217;s to fun, alcohol free drinks! I hope you all have a very happy new year! </p>


<div id="wprm-recipe-container-25670" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="25670" data-servings="0"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
    <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img decoding="async" decoding=async style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-340x340.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt="" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-340x340.jpg 340w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/finished-syrup-under-tree-500x500.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/recipe/mulled-apple-cider-syrup/?tp_image_id=25666" /></div>
</div>
