      <dc:creator><![CDATA[Marisa McClellan]]></dc:creator>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Dec 2021 03:35:18 +0000</pubDate>
      <category><![CDATA[jar love]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Ball Home Canning]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[storage]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://foodinjars.com/?p=25492</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Cleaning and reorganizing my spice shelf using a whole bunch of Ball Mini Storage Jars has left me with a storage solution that is beautiful and easy to use! This post is sponsored by the makers ofBall home canning products.* The week before Scott and I got married, my dad cut a hole in my [&#8230;]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><em>Cleaning and reorganizing my spice shelf using a whole bunch of Ball Mini Storage Jars has left me with a storage solution that is beautiful and easy to use! </em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/spice-shelf-overhaul-with-ball-mini-storage-jars/?tp_image_id=25479" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-1060x1060.jpg" alt="Image of wooden shelves lined with Ball Mini Storage Jars filled with spices and dried herbs. " class="wp-image-25479" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-1060x1060.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-720x720.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-340x340.jpg 340w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-768x768.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square-500x500.jpg 500w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/spices-after-square.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p><em>This post is sponsored by the makers of<a href="https://www.freshpreserving.com/" rel="sponsored nofollow">Ball home canning products.</a>*</em></p>



<p>The week before Scott and I got married, my dad cut a hole in my kitchen wall and built a massive spice shelf into the space he carved out. As soon as he put the final shelf into place, I filled up those shelves with jars of spices and never looked back. </p>



<p>That was a little over 12 years ago now. I&#8217;m embarrassed to admit that in the intervening years, I&#8217;ve never taken everything down, purged spices, and thoroughly cleaned the shelves. I&#8217;ve spot cleaned on an as-needed basis, but it was just never a priority. However, lately I&#8217;ve been trying to tackle these small projects. It gives me a sense of accomplishment in season of life where there&#8217;s not a whole lot of that. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="795" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/spice-shelf-overhaul-with-ball-mini-storage-jars/?tp_image_id=25615" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-795x1060.jpeg" alt="Overhead image of spice jars before cleaning and decanting. " class="wp-image-25615" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-795x1060.jpeg 795w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-540x720.jpeg 540w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-1152x1536.jpeg 1152w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-1536x2048.jpeg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/overhead-of-spices-on-counter-scaled.jpeg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></figure>



<p>I started by pulling every jar, tin, and bag down so that I could see what I had. Once the shelves were empty, I took the boards down and scrubbed them in the sink. I wanted the cleanest slate I could get.</p>



<p>I discovered that I had three jars of oregano, another three of turmeric, and two of ground nutmeg (which is particularly weird, since I typically use freshly grated). Once I purged and grouped the various spices, I started decanting and consolidating. I used more than a dozen <a href="https://bit.ly/3G37vyD" rel="sponsored nofollow">Ball Mini Storage Jars</a> for my smaller quantity spices. They hold 4 ounces and look like mini pint jars. They aren&#8217;t safe for canning, but they do a great job of keeping herbs and spices neatly contained and easily to hand. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="795" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/spice-shelf-overhaul-with-ball-mini-storage-jars/?tp_image_id=25489" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-1060x795.jpg" alt="Close up of Ball Mini Storage Jars filled with spices. " class="wp-image-25489" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-1060x795.jpg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-720x540.jpg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-768x576.jpg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/close-on-ball-spice-jars-500x375.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>I keep some spices in larger quantities than fit into those cute <meta charset="utf-8">Ball Mini Storage Jars, and so I also used a some Ball Smooth Sided Pint Jars and a handful of <meta charset="utf-8">Ball Wide Mouth Quarts. I love how uniform everything looks. It&#8217;s a big step up from my previous hodgepodge of jars, boxes, and tins. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1060" height="1060" decoding=async data-pin-url="https://foodinjars.com/blog/spice-shelf-overhaul-with-ball-mini-storage-jars/?tp_image_id=25616" src="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-1060x1060.jpeg" alt="Image of larger Ball jars filled with larger quantities of spices. " class="wp-image-25616" srcset="https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-1060x1060.jpeg 1060w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-720x720.jpeg 720w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-340x340.jpeg 340w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-1536x1536.jpeg 1536w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-2048x2048.jpeg 2048w, https://foodinjars.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PIC_0966-500x500.jpeg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px" /></figure>



<p>Having my spices cleaned, sorted, and organized feels amazing. I feel like holiday cooking and baking will be much more pleasant and satisfying this year than it would have been otherwise. </p>



<p>Do you have a cleaning project that leaves you with a similar sense of satisfaction? I&#8217;ve love to hear about it! </p>



